tissueExpression.summary: Pancreatic islets, gastric chief cells and the thyroid gland showed strong cytoplasmic staining. Distinct nuclear immunoreactivity was observed in subsets of seminiferous duct cells in testis. Remaining normal cells showed staining or were negative.

subcellularLocation.summary: Mainly localized to the nucleus but excluded from the nucleoli. In addition localized to the cytoplasm.

tissueExpression.summary: Pancreatic islets, gastric chief cells and the thyroid gland showed strong cytoplasmic staining. Distinct nuclear immunoreactivity was observed in subsets of seminiferous duct cells in testis. Remaining normal cells showed staining or were negative.
Malignant cells were in general weakly stained or negative. Several testicular cancers as well as a few cholangiocarcinomas and pancreatic cancers showed moderately staining.
